    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-25T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-25T07:00:00-05:00" n="809"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/4–2554: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 809<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            type="from">Caffery</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d809fn1">Repeated to Tel Aviv as telegram 74.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-25T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 25, 1954—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1348. Re Tel Aviv telegram 1071.<note n="2" xml:id="d809fn2">
                        <ref target="#d798">Document 798</ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RGM1">Riad</persName> told Embassy officer yesterday he or
                        <persName corresp="#p_GLCS1">Gohar</persName> prepared meet Israelis
                    opposite number any time for informal discussion border problems with or without
                    local commanders and police participation and in presence <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> observer. <pb facs="1571" n="1531" xml:id="pg_1531"/>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RGM1">Riad</persName> said such meetings had been
                    suggested many times, most recently to <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>
                    chairman <persName corresp="#p_HCT1">Hinkle</persName> who approved, but fact
                    that nothing ever came of suggestions showed Israelis seek political or
                    propaganda advantage from border situation and have no genuine desire reduce
                    incidents. Nevertheless, Egypt always prepared cooperate immediately in any such
                    meeting.</p>
                <p>Israeli concept of purpose such meeting as described reference telegram was not
                    conveyed to <persName corresp="#p_RGM1">Riad</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
